TASK 2 - CLIENT-SERVER MODEL
1. Client
Client wo computer ya application hota hai jo server se service ya resource request karta hai.
Important: Client hamesha request initiate karta hai.
Examples:
•	Web Browser
•	Mobile App
•	Email Client
Example:
Tum Chrome mein Google open karte ho → Chrome Client hai.
________________________________________
2. Server
Server wo computer/system hota hai jo client ki request ko receive karke requested service ya resource provide karta hai.
Example:
Tum website open karte ho → Website ko host karne wala system Server hai.
Simple Flow:
Client → Request → Server
Client ← Response ← Server
Example:
Browser → Website Request → Web Server
Browser ← Webpage Response ← Web Server
________________________________________
3. Request & Response
Request
Client server ko koi resource ya service maangne ke liye Request bhejta hai.
Response
Server request ko process karke client ko Response bhejta hai.
Agar request incorrect ho ya resource available na ho, to server Error Response de sakta hai.
Example:
Browser → "Mujhe Google ka webpage chahiye."
Server → "Ye lo webpage."
Important:
Client = Request karta hai
Server = Response deta hai
________________________________________
4. Protocol
Protocol rules ka ek set hota hai jo define karta hai ki client aur server aapas mein kaise communicate karenge.
Protocol define karta hai:
•	Kaunse commands use honge.
•	Request ka format kya hoga.
•	Syntax kya hoga.
•	Server ko kis request par kya response dena hai.
•	Galat request par kya response dena hai.
Example: HTTP ek protocol hai jo web browsers aur web servers ke communication mein use hota hai.
Simple Definition:
Protocol = Communication ke Rules
________________________________________
5. Port
Port server par running kisi specific service ko identify karta hai.
Ek server par multiple services chal sakti hain aur har service alag port par listen kar sakti hai.
Example:
Server:
•	Web Service → Port 80
•	HTTPS Service → Port 443
•	SSH Service → Port 22
Agar client ko kisi specific service se connect karna hai, to usse correct port par connect karna hota hai.
Simple Example:
Server = Building
Port = Different Doors
Service = Door ke andar available service
Port = Specific Service ka Entry Point
________________________________________
6. DNS
DNS = Domain Name System
DNS website ke domain name ko IP address mein resolve karta hai.
Hum website ka naam easily remember kar sakte hain, jaise:
example.com
Lekin computers network par server ko locate karne ke liye IP address ka use karte hain.
DNS domain name ko corresponding IP address se resolve karta hai.
Example:
google.com
↓ DNS
IP Address
Simple Example:
DNS = Internet ka GPS/Phonebook
Jaise GPS naam ya location se destination find karne mein help karta hai, waise DNS domain name se server ka IP address find karta hai.
________________________________________
7. IP Address
IP Address network par kisi device/server ka address hota hai.
Ye devices ko identify aur locate karne mein help karta hai.
Example:
192.168.1.10
Simple Definition:
IP Address = Network par device ka address
________________________________________
8. Network
Network multiple computers/devices ka connection hai jo data aur resources share karne ke liye connected hote hain.
Example:
•	Home Wi-Fi Network
•	Office Network
•	Internet
________________________________________
COMPLETE CLIENT-SERVER FLOW
Jab tum browser mein website open karte ho:
1. Client (Browser)
↓
2. DNS domain name ko IP Address mein resolve karta hai
↓
3. Client correct Port par Server se connect karta hai
↓
4. Client Request bhejta hai
↓
5. Server Request process karta hai
↓
6. Server Response bhejta hai
↓
7. Browser Response ko display karta hai
Example:
You → Chrome → DNS → IP Address → Server → Request → Response → Webpage
