TASK 3 - WEB COMMUNICATION IN PRACTICE
1. HTTP / HTTPS
HTTP = Hypertext Transfer Protocol
HTTPS = Hypertext Transfer Protocol Secure
HTTP/HTTPS ek stateless client-server protocol hai jo World Wide Web par communication ke liye use hota hai.
Stateless ka matlab: Server normally har request ko independently process karta hai aur previous requests ki information automatically remember nahi karta.
Example:
Browser (Client) → HTTP Request → Web Server
Web Server → HTTP Response → Browser
________________________________________
2. Stateful Mechanism
HTTP stateless hai, lekin websites application-level mechanisms se user ka state maintain kar sakti hain.
Example: Login karne ke baad website ek session ID, cookie ya token use karti hai.
Iski wajah se tumhe har request par dobara login nahi karna padta.
Simple:
HTTP = Stateless
Cookies / Tokens / Sessions = User State Maintain karne mein help
________________________________________
3. HTTP Methods
HTTP mein commands ko Methods kaha jata hai.
9 Core HTTP Methods:
•	GET
•	POST
•	PUT
•	DELETE
•	PATCH
•	HEAD
•	OPTIONS
•	CONNECT
•	TRACE
Important Methods:
GET → Server se resource/data retrieve karna
POST → Data server ko send karna
PUT → Resource ko update/replace karna
DELETE → Resource delete karna
PATCH → Resource ka partial update
Important:
Is task mein mainly GET method par focus kiya gaya hai.
________________________________________
4. GET Method
GET method ka use web server se resource retrieve karne ke liye hota hai.
Example:
GET https://tryhackme.com/index.php
Iska matlab server se index.php resource request karna.
Jab tum browser mein website ka URL enter karte ho, browser background mein HTTP GET request create karke server ko bhej sakta hai.
Flow:
Browser (Client)
↓
GET Request
↓
Web Server
↓
Response + Status Code + Requested Data
↓
Browser
________________________________________
5. HTTP Request
HTTP Request wo message hai jo client server ko bhejta hai kisi resource ya service ko request karne ke liye.
Example:
Browser → "Mujhe website ka homepage chahiye."
Server request receive karta hai aur response bhejta hai.
________________________________________
6. HTTP Response
Server client ki request process karne ke baad HTTP Response send karta hai.
Response ke mainly 2 important parts hote hain:
Response Header
Response ke baare mein metadata/information contain karta hai.
Response Body
Requested actual content/data contain karta hai.
Example: Webpage ka HTML response body mein ho sakta hai.
________________________________________
7. Important GET Request Fields
Scheme
Batata hai ki kaunsa protocol use ho raha hai.
Examples:
http
https
________________________________________
Host
Batata hai ki request kis website/server ke host name ko ki gayi hai.
Example:
https://www.iamlearning.thm/contact
Host = www.iamlearning.thm
________________________________________
Filename
Batata hai ki host se kaunsa resource/file request kiya gaya hai.
Example:
https://example.com/index.html
Filename = index.html
Agar URL ke end mein / ho, to generally default page jaise index.html serve ho sakta hai.
________________________________________
Address
Website/server ka IP Address show karta hai.
Example:
127.0.0.1
127.0.0.1 ko localhost kaha jata hai, yani same machine/device.
________________________________________
Status Code
Batata hai ki request ka result kya raha.
Common Status Codes:
200 OK → Request successful
404 Not Found → Resource nahi mila
403 Forbidden → Access denied
500 Internal Server Error → Server-side error
________________________________________
8. Browser Developer Tools
Browser ke Developer Tools se hum website ke requests aur responses inspect kar sakte hain.
Network tab mein hum dekh sakte hain:
•	HTTP Requests
•	HTTP Responses
•	GET Requests
•	Status Codes
•	Headers
•	Response Data
Cybersecurity mein importance: Web traffic ko understand aur analyze karne ke liye Developer Tools useful hain.
________________________________________
