TRYHACKME QUESTIONS & ANSWERS
Q1. What does HTTP stand for?
Ans: Hypertext Transfer Protocol
Q2. What does HTTPS stand for?
Ans: Hypertext Transfer Protocol Secure
Q3. Is HTTP stateful or stateless?
Ans: Stateless
Q4. What does stateless mean?
Ans: Each request is processed independently without the server automatically retaining information about previous requests.
Q5. Name the 9 core HTTP methods.
Ans: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, HEAD, OPTIONS, CONNECT, TRACE
Q6. What is the purpose of the GET method?
Ans: To retrieve a resource from a web server.
Q7. What are the two main parts of an HTTP response?
Ans: Response Header and Response Body
Q8. What does the Response Header contain?
Ans: Metadata about the response.
Q9. What does the Response Body contain?
Ans: The requested content/data.
Q10. What does the Scheme tell us?
Ans: Which protocol is being used, such as HTTP or HTTPS.
Q11. What does the Host tell us?
Ans: The name of the host/server from which resources are requested.
Q12. What does the Address field show?
Ans: The IP address where the website is hosted.
Q13. What does HTTP status code 200 OK mean?
Ans: The request was successful.
Q14. What would be the host in the following URL?
https://www.iamlearning.thm/contact
Ans: www.iamlearning.thm
Q15. What would be the scheme in the following URL?
https://www.iamlearning.thm/contact
